 group of fighters (”roughs”)-a dynamic that often resulted in violence and even death. Challenges, fights, and duels were common. Based on extensive research into heretofore ignored primary sources-courts-martial records and regimental order books-The Gentlemen and the Roughs uncovers holes in our understanding of the men who fought the Civil War and the society that produced them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHonorzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aMasculinityzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aSocial classeszUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aSocial conflictzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aSoldierszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy19th century. 0aViolencezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / Civil War Period (1850-1877).2bisacsh  a1865.  aCivil.  aConfederates.  aDuring.  aGentlemen.  aInternal.  aNorths.  aRoughs.  aSouthern.  aUnion.  aWar.  aagainst.  aantagonisms.  aarmy.  aarmylike.  abelow.  abooksThe.  abubbled.  aclaim.  aclass.  acohesive.  aconflicting.  adifferences.  adistracted.  adivisions.  aenough.  aextensive.  afissures.  afought.  afour.  afractiousness.  afrom.  afront.  agrueling.  aheretofore.  aholes.  aideological.  aignored.  ainto.  aorder.  apersonalities.  apresumably.  aprimary.  aproduced.  aquelling.  arebellionBased.  arecords.  aregimental.  aregional.  aresearch.  arife.  asociety.  asourcescourts-martial.  asprangappeared.  asurface.  athat.  athem.  auncovers.  aunderstanding.  aunited.  avictory.  awere.  awhich.  awithin.  awithstand.  ayears.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz